snippet.textDisplay: Charlize Theron´s sage comments with respect to Non-Disclosure Agreements (NDA) are poignant and worthy of profound deliberation by lawmakers.  While it is true NDAs are achieved with the agreement of the parties concerned and facilitate settlement (both positive in the short-term), they perpetuate a culture of silence and non-transparency (both negative in the long-term).  I firmly believe no one, ever, should be silenced, whether by direct threat, indirect consequences or, as here, by mutual accord.  The day may come when a majority will agree with this - and I certainly do hope this will come to be, and soon, for the good of humanity and justice.
